The paper deals with the design of inner codes for reliable data transmission in multi-hop wireless networks, which is a problem related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The optimization problem formulated in the paper is a mixed integer nonlinear programming (MINLP) problem, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes both centralized and decentralized optimization strategies, which involve machine learning techniques and look-up tables, respectively, and thus may be relevant to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
